* {{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=Jump Force Game Adds My Hero Academia's All Might|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-11/jump-force-game-adds-my-hero-academia-all-might/.145601|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 11, 2019|access-date=April 11, 2019|archive-date=April 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411200711/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-11/jump-force-game-adds-my-hero-academia-all-might/.145601|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=Jump Force Game Previews Katsuki Bakugo in Video|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-05/jump-force-game-previews-katsuki-bakugo-in-video/.148704|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 5, 2019|access-date=July 6, 2019|archive-date=July 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706033143/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-05/jump-force-game-previews-katsuki-bakugo-in-video/.148704|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Moyse|first=Chris|title=Jump Force welcomes My Hero Academia's Shoto Todoroki next week|url=https://www.destructoid.com/jump-force-welcomes-my-hero-academias-shoto-todoroki-next-week/|website=[[Destructoid]]|date=May 20, 2020|access-date=December 30, 2022|archive-date=December 30, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221230003543/https://www.destructoid.com/jump-force-welcomes-my-hero-academias-shoto-todoroki-next-week/|url-status=live}}</ref> Izuku Midoriya, Katsuki Bakugo, [[Ochaco Uraraka]], All Might, Shoto Todoroki, [[Eijiro Kirishima]], [[Mina Ashido]], and the members of [[List of My Hero Academia characters#League of Villains|League of Villains]] appeared as cosmetic outfits for players to purchase in ''[[Fortnite]]''. Additionally, the in-game abilities including "Deku's Smash" and "Todoroki's Ice Wall" were introduced.<ref>''Fortnite Battle Royale'' collaboration:
* {{Cite web|last=Luster|first=Joseph|title=Fortnite Launches My Hero Academia Collaboration on December 16|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2022/12/11/fortnite-launches-my-hero-academia-collaboration-on-december-16|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=December 11, 2022|access-date=December 11, 2022|archive-date=December 11, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221211213459/https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2022/12/11/fortnite-launches-my-hero-academia-collaboration-on-december-16|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|title=Become a Hero with Fortnite x My Hero Academia!|url=https://www.epicgames.com/fortnite/en-US/news/become-a-hero-with-fortnite-x-my-hero-academia|website=Epic Games' Fortnite|date=December 16, 2022|access-date=December 16, 2022|archive-date=December 16, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221216220541/https://www.epicgames.com/fortnite/en-US/news/become-a-hero-with-fortnite-x-my-hero-academia|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Luster|first=Joseph|title=My Hero Academia Fortnite Collab Returns with Shoto Todoroki and More|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2023/9/12/my-hero-academia-fortnite-collab-returns-with-shoto-todoroki-and-more|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=September 12, 2023|access-date=September 12, 2023|archive-date=July 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240705180247/https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2023/9/12/my-hero-academia-fortnite-collab-returns-with-shoto-todoroki-and-more|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Cardine|first=Kyle|title=My Hero Academia Fortnite Collab Releases the League of Villains Collection|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2024/5/11/my-hero-academia-fortnite-shigaraki-dabi-toga|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=May 11, 2024|access-date=May 21, 2024|archive-date=May 21, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240521052754/https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2024/5/11/my-hero-academia-fortnite-shigaraki-dabi-toga|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2023, a [[Roblox]] game based on the anime, ''My Hero Academia: Battlegrounds'', was produced by [[Gamefam]] in collaboration with [[Crunchyroll]] and [[Toho]];<ref>{{Cite web|last=Luster|first=Joseph|title=My Hero Academia Battlegrounds Roblox Beta Goes Live as Service's 1st Official Anime Game|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2023/12/21/my-hero-academia-roblox-beta-anime-game|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=December 21, 2023|access-date=October 14, 2024|archive-date=July 9, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240709081005/https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2023/12/21/my-hero-academia-roblox-beta-anime-game|url-status=live}}</ref> and in September 2025, its second game ''My Hero Academia: Ultimate'' was also developed by Gamefam in collaboration with Crunchyroll.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bonthuys|first=Darryn|title=A New My Hero Academia MMORPG Is Headed To Roblox Very Soon|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/a-new-my-hero-academia-mmorpg-is-headed-to-roblox-very-soon/1100-6534489/|website=[[GameSpot]]|date=September 5, 2025|access-date=September 5, 2025|archive-date=September 5, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250905232025/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/a-new-my-hero-academia-mmorpg-is-headed-to-roblox-very-soon/1100-6534489/|url-status=live}}</ref> Izuku and Katsuki were featured as playable characters in the ''[[Granblue Fantasy]]'' collaboration event from January 12–25, 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Iikura-Gross|first=Ken|title=Granblue Fantasy Set to Cross Over with My Hero Academia|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-01-02/granblue-fantasy-set-to-cross-over-with-my-hero-academia/.206037|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 2, 2024|access-date=September 28, 2024|archive-date=January 20, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240120093614/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-01-02/granblue-fantasy-set-to-cross-over-with-my-hero-academia/.206037|url-status=live}}</ref> A collaboration with ''[[Overwatch 2]]'' became available from October 17–30, 2024. The outfit skins featured [[Tracer (Overwatch)|Tracer]] as Deku, [[Juno (Overwatch)|Juno]] as Uravity, [[Reinhardt (Overwatch)|Reinhardt]] as All Might, [[Kiriko (Overwatch)|Kiriko]] as [[Himiko Toga]], and [[Reaper (Overwatch)|Reaper]] as [[Tomura Shigaraki]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Luster|first=Joseph|title=Overwatch 2 x My Hero Academia Collaboration Goes Live This October|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2024/9/26/overwatch-2-my-hero-academia-collaboration|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=September 26, 2024|access-date=September 28, 2024|archive-date=September 5, 2025|archive-url=https://archive.today/20250905232319/https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2024/9/26/overwatch-2-my-hero-academia-collaboration|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Stage plays ===
''My Hero Academia: The "Ultra" Stage'', a stage play adaptation, was first announced in 2018 and ran from April 12–21 and April 26–29, 2019.<ref name="musical1">{{Cite news|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=My Hero Academia Manga Gets Stage Play Next Spring|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-25/my-hero-academia-manga-gets-stage-play-next-spring/.139891|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 25, 2018|access-date=January 13, 2020|archive-date=January 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113193111/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-25/my-hero-academia-manga-gets-stage-play-next-spring/.139891|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="musical2">{{Cite news|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|title=My Hero Academia Stage Play's Cast, Visual, Debut Dates Revealed|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-12-21/my-hero-academia-stage-play-cast-visual-debut-dates-revealed/.141138|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 21, 2018|access-date=January 13, 2020|archive-date=January 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113194046/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-12-21/my-hero-academia-stage-play-cast-visual-debut-dates-revealed/.141138|url-status=live}}</ref> The play was directed by Tsuneyasu Motoyoshi,<ref name="musical1"/> written by Hideyuki Nishimori, and choreographed by Umebō. Shunsuke Wada composed the music. The cast includes Shin Tamura as Izuku Midoriya, Ryōta Kobayashi as Katsuki Bakugo, Yume Takuchi as Ochako Uraraka, [[Hiroki Ino]] as Tenya Iida, and Ryō Kitamura as Shoto Todoroki.<ref name="musical2"/>

A second stage play adaptation, titled ''My Hero Academia: The "Ultra" Stage: A True Hero'', was scheduled to run from March 6–22 and March 27 – April 5, 2020, with the cast and staff returning.<ref>''The "Ultra" Stage: A True Hero'' stage play:
* {{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Inspires 2nd Stage Play in Spring 2020|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-11/my-hero-academia-inspires-2nd-stage-play-in-spring-2020/.152164|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 11, 2019|access-date=January 13, 2020|archive-date=December 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220041221/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-11/my-hero-academia-inspires-2nd-stage-play-in-spring-2020/.152164|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|title=2nd My Hero Academia Stage Play Unveils Ad, 2 New Visuals|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-01/2nd-my-hero-academia-stage-play-unveils-ad-2-new-visuals/.153871|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 1, 2019|access-date=January 13, 2020|archive-date=January 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114022308/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-01/2nd-my-hero-academia-stage-play-unveils-ad-2-new-visuals/.153871|url-status=live}}</ref> However, due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], ''My Hero Academia: The "Ultra" Stage: A True Hero''{{'}}s original run was canceled and postponed to July 2020, where a complete version, titled ''My Hero Academia: The "Ultra" Stage: A True Hero Plus Stage Ver.'', ran instead.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sherman|first=Jennifer|title=My Hero Academia's Canceled Stage Play Gets New Version in July|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-04-06/my-hero-academia-canceled-stage-play-gets-new-version-in-july/.158344|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 6, 2020|access-date=April 6, 2020|archive-date=April 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406160113/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-04-06/my-hero-academia-canceled-stage-play-gets-new-version-in-july/.158344|url-status=live}}</ref> After one staff member contracted COVID-19, the production committee announced that ''My Hero Academia: The "Ultra" Stage: A True Hero'' would instead be live-streamed; however, the play was delayed again after another staff member contracted COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|title=My Hero Academia Stage Play Delayed After 2 Diagnosed With COVID-19|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-07-14/my-hero-academia-stage-play-delayed-after-2-diagnosed-with-covid-19/.161838|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 14, 2020|access-date=July 14, 2020|archive-date=July 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200715032147/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-07-14/my-hero-academia-stage-play-delayed-after-2-diagnosed-with-covid-19/.161838|url-status=live}}</ref> The stage play ran in 2021 from December 3–12 and December 24–26.<ref>''A True Hero Plus Stage Ver.'' stage play:
* {{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Stage Play Gets New Run in 2021|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-12-19/my-hero-academia-stage-play-gets-new-run-in-2021/.167632|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 19, 2020|access-date=December 19, 2020|archive-date=March 4, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304110053/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-12-19/my-hero-academia-stage-play-gets-new-run-in-2021/.167632|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Gets New Stage Play in Spring 2022|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-08-22/my-hero-academia-gets-new-stage-play-in-spring-2022/.176519|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 22, 2021|access-date=August 22, 2021|archive-date=June 27, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220627103403/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-08-22/my-hero-academia-gets-new-stage-play-in-spring-2022/.176519|url-status=live}}</ref>

A third stage play adaptation titled ''My Hero Academia The "Ultra" Stage: The Symbol of Peace'' was announced on December 26, 2021, and was scheduled to run from April 9–10, April 22–24, and April 29 – May 8, 2022.<ref>''The "Ultra" Stage: The Symbol of Peace'' stage play:
* {{Cite web|last=Komatsu|first=Mikikazu|title=My Hero Academia 3rd Stage Play "The Symbol of Peace" Slated for Spring 2022|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2021/12/26-1/my-hero-academia-3rd-stage-play-the-symbol-of-peace-slated-for-spring-2022|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=December 26, 2021|access-date=December 27, 2021|archive-date=December 28, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211228135726/https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2021/12/26-1/my-hero-academia-3rd-stage-play-the-symbol-of-peace-slated-for-spring-2022|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia's New Stage Play Runs in 3 Cities in April, May|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-01-02/my-hero-academia-new-stage-play-runs-in-3-cities-in-april-may/.181168|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 2, 2022|access-date=January 3, 2022|archive-date=April 25, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425092849/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-01-02/my-hero-academia-new-stage-play-runs-in-3-cities-in-april-may/.181168|url-status=live}}</ref> However, due to one of the actor's injury during a performance of the play, future performances were postponed.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hazra|first=Adriana|title=My Hero Academia Stage Play Cancels 3 Performances Due to Actor's Injury|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-04-25/my-hero-academia-stage-play-cancels-3-performances-due-to-actor-injury/.184959|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 25, 2022|access-date=April 26, 2022|archive-date=May 20, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220520062335/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-04-25/my-hero-academia-stage-play-cancels-3-performances-due-to-actor-injury/.184959|url-status=live}}</ref>

A fourth stage play adaptation, titled ''My Hero Academia: The "Ultra" Stage: The Best Hero'', was announced at the Jump Festa '23 event in December 2022. It ran from April 29 – May 7, May 12–14, and May 19–21, 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Gets New Stage Play in April–May 2023|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-12-17/my-hero-academia-gets-new-stage-play-in-april-may-2023/.193059|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 17, 2022|access-date=December 20, 2022|archive-date=December 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221219074216/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-12-17/my-hero-academia-gets-new-stage-play-in-april-may-2023/.193059|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Art and guidebooks ===
Two ''My Hero Academia'' [[Artist's book|art books]] and three [[Guide book|guidebooks]] have been released by Shueisha. The first art book, titled {{nihongo|''My Hero Academia: Official Character Guide Ultra Archive Art Book''|僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式キャラクターガイド ウルトラアーカイブ画集|Boku no Hīrō Akademia Kōshiki Kyarakutā Gaido Urutora Ākaibu Gashū}}, was released on May 7, 2016.<ref>{{Cite book|title=MY HERO ACADEMIA OFFICIAL CHARACTER BOOK ULTRA ARCHIVE (ARTBOOK VO JAPONAIS)|publisher=[[Amazon (company)|Amazon]]|isbn=978-4-08-880719-5|date=May 2016}}</ref> The first guidebook, titled {{nihongo foot|''My Hero Academia: Ultra Archive - The Official Character Guide'',|僕のヒーローアカデミア公式キャラクターブック Ultra Archive|Boku no Hīrō Akademia Kōshiki Kyarakutā Bukku Urutora Ākaibu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} was published on May 2, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:僕のヒーローアカデミア公式キャラクターブック Ultra Archive|url=https://www.s-manga.net/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-880719-5|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|access-date=May 2, 2016|language=ja|archive-date=August 29, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220829083156/https://www.s-manga.net/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-880719-5|url-status=live}}</ref> Accompanying the anime, the second guidebook, titled {{nihongo foot|''My Hero Academia: Ultimate Animation – The Official Book Guide'',|僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式ガイドブック Ultimate Animation Guide|Boku no Hīrō Akademia Kōshiki Gaido Bukku Arutimetto Animēshon|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} was released on September 4, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:TVアニメ 僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式ガイドブック Ultimate Animation Guide|url=https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-881258-8|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|access-date=September 4, 2017|language=ja|archive-date=August 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220824101437/https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-881258-8|url-status=live}}</ref> The third guidebook, titled {{nihongo foot|''My Hero Academia: Ultra Analysis – The Official Character Guide'',|僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式キャラクターブック2 Ultra Analysis|Boku no Hīrō Akademia Kōshiki Kyarakutā Bukku 2 Urutora Anarishisu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} was released on October 4, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式キャラクターブック2 Ultra Analysis|url=https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-882128-3|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|access-date=October 4, 2019|language=ja|archive-date=June 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220604004207/https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-882128-3|url-status=live}}</ref> The second and final artbook, titled {{nihongo foot|''My Hero Academia: Official Illustration Collection Ultra Artworks'',|僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式イラスト集 Ultra Artworks|Boku no Hīrō Akademia Kōshiki Irasuto-shū Urutora Ātowākusu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} was released on June 4, 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:僕のヒーローアカデミア 公式イラスト集 Ultra Artworks|url=https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-792621-7|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|access-date=February 22, 2025|language=ja|archive-date=February 22, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222062844/https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-792621-7|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Other media ===
A [[Radio drama in Japan|drama CD]] titled {{nihongo|''My Hero Academia: Sweep! Local Area Cleaning!''|僕のヒーローアカデミアハケ！ちいきせいそう！|Boku no Hīrō Akademia Hake! Chiiki Seisou!}} bundled with a limited edition of the seventh volume of the manga, released before the anime. Kōhei Horikoshi provides the original story and supervised the project, and the script is written by Yōsuke Kuroda who also wrote for the anime series.<ref name="cast"/><ref>{{Cite web|last=Komatsu|first=Mikikazu|title=VIDEO: Preview for "My Hero Academia" Drama CD Featuring Anime Voice Cast|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/01/25-1/video-preview-for-my-hero-academia-drama-cd-featuring-anime-voice-cast|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=January 25, 2016|access-date=January 26, 2016|archive-date=January 28, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128123607/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/01/25-1/video-preview-for-my-hero-academia-drama-cd-featuring-anime-voice-cast|url-status=live}}</ref> An interactive puzzle-solving event called "Heroes Dead End Program" was held on July 29 and 30, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Whalen|first=Amanda|title=Fans Can Manifest Quirks, Fight Villains at My Hero Academia Event in July|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2017-04-20/fans-can-manifest-quirks-fight-villains-at-my-hero-academia-event-in-july/.114941|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 20, 2017|access-date=January 30, 2023|archive-date=June 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220624234940/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2017-04-20/fans-can-manifest-quirks-fight-villains-at-my-hero-academia-event-in-july/.114941|url-status=live}}</ref> An [[Exhibition|exhibit]] of the series ran in [[Tokyo]]'s [[Sunshine City, Tokyo|Ikebukuro Sunshine City]] from September 30 to October 8, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Morrissy|first=Kim|title=My Hero Academia Exhibit Takes You Through the Anime Locations|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2018-10-02/my-hero-academia-exhibit-takes-you-through-the-anime-locations/.137596|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 2, 2018|access-date=October 3, 2018|archive-date=January 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126005955/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2018-10-02/my-hero-academia-exhibit-takes-you-through-the-anime-locations/.137596|url-status=live}}</ref>

An [[art exhibition]], titled "My Hero Academia Drawing Smash", ran in Tokyo from April 23 to June 27, 2021, and in [[Osaka]] from July 16 to September 5, 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:ヒロアカ初の原画展、東京・大阪で来年開催！堀越耕平描き下ろしキービジュ公開|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/407698|website=[[Comic Natalie]]|publisher=Natasha, Inc|date=December 7, 2020|access-date=March 25, 2023|language=ja|archive-date=January 22, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122231333/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/407698|url-status=live}}</ref> An animation exhibition with a theme of Heroes vs. Villains, titled ''My Hero Academia Anime: All-Out War Arc Exhibition'', ran in various cities in Japan from April to November 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:『僕のヒーローアカデミア』ANIMATION展 -全面戦争編-」|url=https://heroaca-anime-ex2023.com/|website=My Hero Academia Anime -All-Out War Arc- Exhibition website|access-date=August 6, 2023|language=ja|archive-date=August 6, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230806224359/https://heroaca-anime-ex2023.com/|url-status=live}}</ref> Another animation exhibition, titled ''My Hero Academia Ultra Animation Exhibition'', ran in Tokyo and Osaka from December 2023 to March 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:TVアニメ『僕のヒーローアカデミア』Ultra Animation Exhibition|url=https://heroaca-uaexhibition.com/|website=My Hero Academia Ultra Animation Exhibition website|access-date=March 6, 2024|language=ja|archive-date=March 6, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240306011602/https://heroaca-uaexhibition.com/|url-status=live}}</ref> Another art exhibition, to celebrate the series' ten-year run, was held at Creative Museum Tokyo from June 21 to August 31, 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tai|first=Anita|title=My Hero Academia Manga's Finale Celebrated With Final Fanbook, 1st Art Book, Art Exhibit|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2024-08-04/my-hero-academia-manga-finale-celebrated-with-final-fanbook-1st-art-book-art-exhibit/.213942|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 4, 2024|access-date=August 4, 2024|archive-date=August 4, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240804210302/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2024-08-04/my-hero-academia-manga-finale-celebrated-with-final-fanbook-1st-art-book-art-exhibit/.213942|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:「僕のヒーローアカデミア」最終42巻の表紙を初公開、原画展のキービジュアルも|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/600044|website=[[Comic Natalie]]|publisher=Natasha, Inc|date=November 20, 2024|access-date=November 20, 2024|language=ja|archive-date=November 20, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241120031531/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/600044|url-status=live}}</p></ref> It is set to be held at the [[Namba Parks|Namba Parks Museum]] in Osaka from October 25 to December 21 of the same year, and in [[Fukuoka]] on Q2 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:「ヒロアカ」原画展、大阪会場の新グッズ＆カフェメニュー発表　2026年春に福岡も巡回|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/638301|website=[[Comic Natalie]]|publisher=Natasha, Inc|date=September 1, 2025|access-date=September 1, 2025|language=ja|archive-date=September 1, 2025|archive-url=https://archive.today/20250901113730/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/638301|url-status=live}}</ref>

From March 1 to August 14, 2024, [[Universal Studios Japan]] hosted an attraction based on the series, as part of the "[[Cool Japan]]" program. ''My Hero Academia The Real 4-D'' attraction uses 3D visuals and special effects such as seat rumbles and splashes of water. It also includes an original story featuring Deku, Bakugo, Uraraka, and Todoroki facing off against a villain who appears at the concert of a world-famous rock performer.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=Universal Studios Japan's New My Hero Academia 4D Attraction Features Original Story|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2023-12-21/universal-studios-japan-new-my-hero-academia-4d-attraction-features-original-story/.205780|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 21, 2023|access-date=December 21, 2023|archive-date=December 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231221235521/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2023-12-21/universal-studios-japan-new-my-hero-academia-4d-attraction-features-original-story/.205780|url-status=live}}</ref> A live-action short film titled "Succession", commemorating the manga's tenth anniversary, released its video on YTV Animation's YouTube channel on April 27, 2024. It follows the lives of two brothers who grew up together with the manga series using its iconic quotes.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:「ヒロアカ」とともに成長した兄弟の姿を描く実写ショートフィルム、音楽は林ゆうき|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/571301|website=[[Comic Natalie]]|publisher=Natasha, Inc|date=April 27, 2024|access-date=May 8, 2024|language=ja|archive-date=May 8, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240508154014/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/571301|url-status=live}}</ref>

A global popularity poll titled "World Best Hero", commemorating the manga's ten-year run, was announced on August 5, 2024. The poll advertisement was published in the International edition of ''[[The New York Times]]'' on August 6. It is the first manga that Shueisha hosted a worldwide character popularity poll. The voting opened till September 30, with the winner on December 3 would get a statue designed by Horikoshi.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Gets 1st Worldwide Character Popularity Poll, Ad in New York Times|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-08-05/my-hero-academia-gets-1st-worldwide-character-popularity-poll-ad-in-new-york-times/.213977|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 5, 2024|access-date=August 14, 2024|archive-date=August 6, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240806175655/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-08-05/my-hero-academia-gets-1st-worldwide-character-popularity-poll-ad-in-new-york-times/.213977|url-status=live}}</ref> A [[wikt:fanbook|fanbook]] titled ''My Hero Academia: Final Fan Book Ultra Age'', to celebrate the manga's completion, was released on May 2, 2025. It includes the detailed information about the characters, setting, quirks, and special moves. It also features an interview with the past editors, a Q&A corner with Horikoshi, and an exclusive short one-shot manga.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:僕のヒーローアカデミア ファイナルファンブック Ultra Age|url=https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-884309-4|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|access-date=February 22, 2025|language=ja|archive-date=February 22, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222064823/https://www.shueisha.co.jp/books/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-884309-4|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Reception ==
[[File:Cosplay of Mina Ashido, All Might, Toshino Yagi, Izuku Midoriya, Gunhead and Ochaco Uraraka from My Hero Academia at FanimeCon 2018 391 (40640213690).jpg|thumb|300px|Fans [[cosplay]]ing as characters from ''My Hero Academia'' at [[FanimeCon]] in 2018]]

=== Popularity ===
''My Hero Academia'' ranked second on the "Nationwide Bookstore Employees' Recommended Comics of 2015" poll by Honya Club online bookstore.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Japanese Bookstores Recommend 15 Top Manga for 2015|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-02-04/japanese-bookstores-recommend-15-top-manga-for-2015/.84088|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 4, 2015|access-date=May 18, 2015|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612031550/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-02-04/japanese-bookstores-recommend-15-top-manga-for-2015/.84088|url-status=live}}</ref> The series has been ranked on the "Book of the Year" list from [[Media Factory]]'s ''[[Da Vinci (magazine)|Da Vinci]]'' magazine, where professional book reviewers, bookstore employees, and ''Da Vinci'' readers participate; it ranked 26th in 2015;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Blyden|first=Jabulani|title=March comes in like a lion Tops Da Vinci Magazine's Rankings for 2015|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-06/march-comes-in-like-a-lion-tops-da-vinci-magazine-rankings-for-2015/.96157|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 6, 2015|access-date=December 7, 2021|archive-date=November 15, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115181852/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-06/march-comes-in-like-a-lion-tops-da-vinci-magazine-rankings-for-2015/.96157|url-status=live}}</ref> 22nd in 2016;<ref name="DaVinci2016"/> 16th in 2018;<ref name="DaVinci2018"/> 37th in 2019;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|title=Kingdom Manga Tops Da Vinci Ranking|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-06/kingdom-manga-tops-da-vinci-ranking/.154037|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 6, 2019|access-date=December 6, 2019|archive-date=March 17, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210317003757/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-06/kingdom-manga-tops-da-vinci-ranking/.154037|url-status=live}}</ref> 41st in 2020;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=Demon Slayer Tops Da Vinci Manga Ranking|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-12-05/demon-slayer-tops-da-vinci-manga-ranking/.167101|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 5, 2020|access-date=December 7, 2021|archive-date=February 17, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210217230911/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-12-05/demon-slayer-tops-da-vinci-manga-ranking/.167101|url-status=live}}</ref> 34th in 2021;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=Demon Slayer Tops Da Vinci Manga Ranking for 2nd Consecutive Year|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-12-06/demon-slayer-tops-da-vinci-manga-ranking-for-2nd-consecutive-year/.180340|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 6, 2021|access-date=December 7, 2021|archive-date=December 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208082249/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-12-06/demon-slayer-tops-da-vinci-manga-ranking-for-2nd-consecutive-year/.180340|url-status=live}}</ref> 22nd in 2022;<ref name="DaVinci2022"/> and 19th in 2024.<ref name="DaVinci2024"/> On [[Takarajimasha]]'s ''[[Kono Manga ga Sugoi!]]'' ranking of the top 20 manga for male readers, it ranked fifth on the 2016 list.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Kono Manga ga Sugoi! Reveals 2016's Series Ranking for Male Readers|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-10/kono-manga-ga-sugoi-reveals-2016-series-ranking-for-male-readers/.96294|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 10, 2015|access-date=June 16, 2022|archive-date=April 25, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425150056/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-10/kono-manga-ga-sugoi-reveals-2016-series-ranking-for-male-readers/.96294|url-status=live}}</ref> On [[TV Asahi]]'s Manga Sōsenkyo 2021 poll, in which 150,000 people voted for their top 100 manga series, ''My Hero Academia'' ranked 16th.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:テレビ朝日『国民15万人がガチで投票!漫画総選挙』ランキング結果まとめ！ 栄えある1位に輝く漫画は!?|url=https://www.animatetimes.com/news/details.php?id=1609599746|website=[[Animate Times]]|publisher=[[Animate (retailer)|Animate]]|date=January 3, 2021|access-date=January 3, 2021|language=ja|archive-date=January 3, 2021|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210103023119/https://www.animatetimes.com/news/details.php?id=1609599746|url-status=live}}</ref> On a 2021 survey conducted by Line Research asking Japanese high school students what manga series they are currently into, the series ranked second among boys.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:【2021年版】高校生がハマっているマンガランキング|url=https://research-platform.line.me/archives/37928113.html|website=Line Research|date=June 1, 2021|access-date=February 11, 2022|language=ja|archive-date=January 27, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127174353/https://research-platform.line.me/archives/37928113.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

The story has been noted to take inspiration from elements in [[superhero comics|American superhero comics]], such as the aesthetics of its characters,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tane|first=Kiyoshi|script-title=ja:『僕のヒーローアカデミア』第1巻 堀越耕平 【日刊マンガガイド】|url=http://konomanga.jp/guide/15859-2|website=[[Kono Manga ga Sugoi!]]|date=November 19, 2014|access-date=December 4, 2014|language=ja|archive-date=December 10, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210142842/http://konomanga.jp/guide/15859-2|url-status=live}}</ref> and due to the popularity of the series, characters of ''My Hero Academia'' were used to promote the [[Marvel Studios]] films ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' and ''[[Captain America: Brave New World]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://manga.tokyo/news/my-hero-academia-x-avengers-collaboration-visual-and-videos/|title=My Hero Academia × Avengers Collaboration Visual and Videos {{!}} MANGA.TOKYO|work=MANGA.TOKYO|date=April 13, 2018|access-date=April 22, 2018|archive-date=April 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180423033950/https://manga.tokyo/news/my-hero-academia-x-avengers-collaboration-visual-and-videos/|url-status=dead}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Iikura-Gross|first=Ken|title=My Hero Academia x Captain America: Brave New World Reveal Collab in Special Promotional Video|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2025-02-06/my-hero-academia-x-captain-america-brave-new-world-reveal-collab-in-special-promotional-video/.220912|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 6, 2025|access-date=February 6, 2025|archive-date=February 6, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250206142124/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2025-02-06/my-hero-academia-x-captain-america-brave-new-world-reveal-collab-in-special-promotional-video/.220912|url-status=live}}</p></ref> Before the anime adaptation's premiere, ''[[Naruto]]''{{'}}s creator [[Masashi Kishimoto]] praised [[Kōhei Horikoshi]]'s work, and said: "''My Hero Academia'' is finally getting animated! Congratulations! To put into words this sensation, which I know firsthand... it's probably a great feeling. [Considering] the original work and the studio, [[Bones (studio)|Bones]]... you don't need the 'probably,' it's a great feeling. People who know it will get it! Internationally, even... in any case, it's a great feeling. It's the same feeling I had when my work was first animated – no, [the series] is more than that! And they aren't making me say this, it's the truth." Kishimoto also believed that it would be a success overseas. ''[[One Piece]]'' creator [[Eiichiro Oda]] also praised the series.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Stimson|first=Eric|title=Naruto Cheers on My Hero Academia's Deku|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2016-04-02/naruto-cheers-on-my-hero-academia-deku/.100428|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 2, 2016|access-date=April 3, 2016|archive-date=April 3, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160403095718/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2016-04-02/naruto-cheers-on-my-hero-academia-deku/.100428|url-status=live}}</ref> After the manga's completion, writers, editors, the anime's staff and cast, and stage play actors expressed congratulations to Horikoshi for his work.<ref>Messages for Horikoshi on Manga's Completion:
* {{Cite web|last=Iikura-Gross|first=Ken|title=My Hero Academia's Kōhei Horikoshi Receives Congratulations From Anime/Manga World|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-08-06/my-hero-academia-kohei-horikoshi-receives-congratulations-from-anime-manga-world/.214018|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 6, 2024|access-date=August 7, 2024|archive-date=August 6, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240806221845/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-08-06/my-hero-academia-kohei-horikoshi-receives-congratulations-from-anime-manga-world/.214018|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Iikura-Gross|first=Ken|title=My Hero Academia Cast Congratulates Kо̄hei Horikoshi on Manga's Completion|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-08-13/my-hero-academia-cast-congratulates-k-hei-horikoshi-on-manga-completion/.214093|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 13, 2024|access-date=August 14, 2024|archive-date=August 14, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240814095539/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2024-08-13/my-hero-academia-cast-congratulates-k-hei-horikoshi-on-manga-completion/.214093|url-status=live}}</ref>

''My Hero Academia'' was popular with Japanese readers of ''Charapedia'', who voted it the fourth best anime show of Q2 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Schley|first=Matt|title=Japanese Fans Choose the Spring 2017 Anime Worth Watching|url=http://otakuusamagazine.com/LatestNews/News1/Japanese-Fans-Choose-the-Spring-2017-Anime-Worth-W-8955.aspx|website=[[Otaku USA]]|date=May 7, 2017|access-date=June 1, 2017|archive-date=June 12, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612041808/http://otakuusamagazine.com/LatestNews/News1/Japanese-Fans-Choose-the-Spring-2017-Anime-Worth-W-8955.aspx|url-status=dead}}</ref> The anime received high TV ratings and has consistently ranked among the top ten animated shows in Japan since the release of its [[My Hero Academia season 2|second season]].<ref>Japanese TV animation weekly ratings in the [[Kantō region]]:
* Episode 13.5: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-30/japan-animation-tv-ranking-march-20-26/.114147|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, March 20–26|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 30, 2017|access-date=July 23, 2017|archive-date=July 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709154426/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-30/japan-animation-tv-ranking-march-20-26/.114147|url-status=live}}
* Episode 14: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-06/japan-animation-tv-ranking-march-27-april-2/.114480|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, March 27 – April 2|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 6, 2017|access-date=July 23, 2017|archive-date=July 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170714155636/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-06/japan-animation-tv-ranking-march-27-april-2/.114480|url-status=live}}
* Episode 15: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-13/japan-animation-tv-ranking-april-3-9/.114760|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, April 3–9|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 13, 2017|access-date=July 23, 2017|archive-date=July 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709163340/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-13/japan-animation-tv-ranking-april-3-9/.114760|url-status=live}}
* Episode 16: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-20/japan-animation-tv-ranking-april-10-16/.115096|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, April 10–16|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 20, 2017|access-date=November 19, 2018|archive-date=November 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101033814/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-20/japan-animation-tv-ranking-april-10-16/.115096|url-status=live}}
* Episode 19: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-18/japan-animation-tv-ranking-may-1-7/.116286|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, May 1–7|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 18, 2017|access-date=July 23, 2017|archive-date=July 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706025750/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-18/japan-animation-tv-ranking-may-1-7/.116286|url-status=live}}
* Episode 20: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-27/japan-animation-tv-ranking-may-8-14/.116669|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, May 8–14|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 27, 2017|access-date=July 23, 2017|archive-date=July 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706030603/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-27/japan-animation-tv-ranking-may-8-14/.116669|url-status=live}}
* Episode 21: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-27/japan-animation-tv-ranking-may-15-21/.116671|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, May 15–21|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 27, 2017|access-date=July 23, 2017|archive-date=July 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706012718/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-27/japan-animation-tv-ranking-may-15-21/.116671|url-status=live}}
