* Episode 37: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-28/japan-animation-tv-ranking-september-17-23/.121997|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, September 17–23|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 28, 2017|access-date=October 2, 2017|archive-date=October 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002171354/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-28/japan-animation-tv-ranking-september-17-23/.121997|url-status=live}}
* Episode 38: {{Cite news|first=Karen|last=Ressler|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-10-05/japan-animation-tv-ranking-september-25-october-1/.122351|title=Japan's Animation TV Ranking, September 25 – October 1|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 5, 2017|access-date=May 15, 2020|archive-date=August 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190813030349/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-10-05/japan-animation-tv-ranking-september-25-october-1/.122351|url-status=live}}</ref> The official music video of the second season's opening theme song, "[[Peace Sign (Kenshi Yonezu song)|Peace Sign]]" by [[Kenshi Yonezu]], reached 48.6 million views on YouTube, becoming one of the top trending videos of 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sherman|first=Jennifer|title=My Hero Academia, Fireworks Top Japan's YouTube Music Videos for 2017|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2017-12-20/my-hero-academia-fireworks-top-japan-youtube-music-videos-for-2017/.125500|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 20, 2017|access-date=March 25, 2023|archive-date=March 14, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230314164433/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2017-12-20/my-hero-academia-fireworks-top-japan-youtube-music-videos-for-2017/.125500|url-status=live}}</ref> In the United States, ''My Hero Academia'' was the second most "in-demand" TV title in the last 60 days in 2020 according to ''[[Observer Media|Observer]]'', which tracks popularity through social media, fan ratings, and piracy.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Morrissy|first=Kim|title=Observer: My Hero Academia Is U.S.'s 2nd Most 'In-Demand' TV Title in Last 60 Days|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2020-07-31/observer-my-hero-academia-is-u.s.s-2nd-most-in-demand-tv-title-in-last-60-days/.162421|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 31, 2020|access-date=August 1, 2020|archive-date=February 9, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209022734/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2020-07-31/observer-my-hero-academia-is-u.s.s-2nd-most-in-demand-tv-title-in-last-60-days/.162421|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2021, it was revealed that the series was the fourth most-watched anime series on [[Crunchyroll]] in 2020, being watched in 23 countries and territories, including North America, Central America, South America, and Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Morrissy|first=Kim|title=Crunchyroll Reveals Most Watched Anime of 2020 by Region|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2021-01-15/crunchyroll-reveals-most-watched-anime-of-2020-by-region/.168432|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 15, 2021|access-date=January 15, 2021|archive-date=January 15, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115214518/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2021-01-15/crunchyroll-reveals-most-watched-anime-of-2020-by-region/.168432|url-status=live}}</ref> In April of the same year, the [[My Hero Academia season 5|fifth season]] of the series set the record for the most-watched premiere of any series on [[MyAnimeList]], surpassing other anime titles such as ''[[Attack on Titan season 4|Attack on Titan: The Final Season]]'', [[The Promised Neverland season 2|''The Promised Neverland'' season 2]], and ''[[Dr. Stone season 2|Dr. Stone: Stone Wars]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Peters|first=Megan|title=My Hero Academia Sets Record with Season 5 Premiere|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-season-5-premiere-record-anime/|website=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=April 4, 2021|access-date=December 2, 2022|archive-date=April 5, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210405223854/https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-season-5-premiere-record-anime/|url-status=live}}</ref>

According to Video Research, the premiere of its [[My Hero Academia season 6|sixth season]] earned a television rating of 3.9% (an improvement from the previous season's 3.2%) and ranked as the fourth-most watched anime, outperforming other popular series such as ''[[One Piece (1999 TV series)|One Piece]]'', ''[[Spy × Family (TV series)|Spy × Family]]'', and ''[[Doraemon (2005 TV series)|Doraemon]]'' in the average household viewership in Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Peters|first=Megan|title=My Hero Academia Season 6 Draws Huge Viewership with Premiere|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-season-6-premiere-ratings/|website=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=October 6, 2022|access-date=December 2, 2022|archive-date=October 18, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221018170420/https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-season-6-premiere-ratings/|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite news|first=Rafael Antonio|last=Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-10-08/japanese-animation-tv-ranking-september-26-october-2/.190593|title=Japanese Animation TV Ranking, September 26 – October 2|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 8, 2022|access-date=October 8, 2022|archive-date=October 9, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221009125954/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-10-08/japanese-animation-tv-ranking-september-26-october-2/.190593|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The sixth season's fifth episode became one of the most-watched episodes of the series, garnering over 3.01 million viewers across 2.26 million households. Additionally, more than 2.64 million people who watched the anime, was an increase of 325,000 viewers from its season premiere, which had an individual viewership rating of 2.1%.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sahu|first=Dharmesh|title=Anime Viewership in Japan: My Hero Academia bags its Biggest Episode Yet|url=https://www.tvfandomlounge.com/2022/11/04/my-hero-academia-season-6-more-anime-viewership/|website=TV Fandom Lounge|date=November 4, 2022|access-date=December 2, 2022|archive-date=November 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221104221824/https://www.tvfandomlounge.com/2022/11/04/my-hero-academia-season-6-more-anime-viewership/|url-status=live}}</ref> By December 22, 2022, the series ranked as the fifth "Most-Watched Anime in Japan" for December 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sahu|first=Dharmesh|title=10 Most-Watched Anime Of December 2022: Spy X Family, Blue Lock, And More|url=https://www.tvfandomlounge.com/most-watched-anime-2022-spy-x-family-blue-lock-more/|website=TV Fandom Lounge|date=December 22, 2022|access-date=March 10, 2023|archive-date=March 10, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230310195822/https://www.tvfandomlounge.com/most-watched-anime-2022-spy-x-family-blue-lock-more/|url-status=live}}</ref> The sixth season's finale averaged 2.01 million viewers on television after its broadcast.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Valdez|first=Nick|title=My Hero Academia Season 6 Finale Ratings Released|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-season-6-finale-ratings/|website=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=April 25, 2023|access-date=April 26, 2023|archive-date=April 26, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426085303/https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-season-6-finale-ratings/|url-status=live}}</ref>

The series' characters have also been highly popular for [[Cosplay|cosplaying]], especially in Japan, where a poll surveyed by Cosplayers Archive ranked ''My Hero Academia'' ninth in Q3 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Schley|first=Matt|title=Japanese Cosplayers Rank the Series They Intend to Cosplay This Summer|url=https://otakuusamagazine.com/japanese-cosplayers-rank-the-series-they-intend-to-cosplay-this-summer/|website=[[Otaku USA]]|date=July 6, 2017|access-date=July 9, 2017|archive-date=May 6, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506182541/https://otakuusamagazine.com/japanese-cosplayers-rank-the-series-they-intend-to-cosplay-this-summer/|url-status=live}}</ref> According to the retailer [[Zavvi (retailer)|Zavvi]], where they surveyed [[Instagram]] hashtags containing franchise names followed by the term "cosplay", ''My Hero Academia'' was the most popular franchise among cosplayers worldwide with 2,377,476 posts, ranking above companies and franchises such as [[DC Comics]], [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]], [[Disney]], ''[[Star Wars]]'', ''Naruto'', ''[[Attack on Titan]]'', ''[[Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba]]'', ''[[Pokémon]]'', and ''[[Sailor Moon]]''. The retailer stated that the result demonstrates the "recent growth of anime". They also surveyed hashtags containing character names, where three ''My Hero Academia'' characters placed in the top ten rankings: [[Izuku Midoriya|Izuku]] ranked fifth with 224,429 posts, [[Shoto Todoroki|Shoto]] came at seventh with 177,161 posts, and [[Katsuki Bakugo|Katsuki]] at ninth with 147,600 posts.<ref>{{Cite web|title=My Hero Academia is The World's Most Popular Franchise to Cosplay!|url=https://blog.funimation.com/2021/09/17/my-hero-academia-is-the-worlds-most-popular-franchise-to-cosplay/|publisher=[[Funimation]]|date=September 17, 2021|access-date=July 9, 2022|archive-date=July 3, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220703062352/https://blog.funimation.com/2021/09/17/my-hero-academia-is-the-worlds-most-popular-franchise-to-cosplay/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On [[Tumblr]]'s Year in Review, which highlights the largest communities, [[fandom]]s, and trends on the platform throughout the year, ''My Hero Academia'' ranked first in the Top Anime & Manga Shows category from 2018 to 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Frank|first=Allegra|title=Tumblr's top anime of the year is a surprising mix of new and old|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/30/18119529/tumblr-top-anime-manga-2018|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|date=November 30, 2018|access-date=February 29, 2024|archive-date=May 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230529112047/https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/30/18119529/tumblr-top-anime-manga-2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="2019YearinReview">{{Cite web|last=Dennison|first=Kara|title=My Hero Academia Rules Tumblr's Anime Fandoms Again in 2019|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2019/12/2/my-hero-academia-rules-tumblrs-anime-fandoms-again-in-2019|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=December 2, 2019|access-date=February 29, 2024|archive-date=February 29, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240229150600/https://www.crunchyroll.com/news/latest/2019/12/2/my-hero-academia-rules-tumblrs-anime-fandoms-again-in-2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="2020YearinReview">{{Cite web|last=Lee|first=Choo Sum|title=My Hero Academia Dominates Tumblr's 2020 Top Anime & Manga List|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2020-12-08/my-hero-academia-dominates-tumblr-2020-top-anime-and-manga-list/.167197|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 8, 2020|access-date=December 15, 2020|archive-date=December 11, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201211133814/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2020-12-08/my-hero-academia-dominates-tumblr-2020-top-anime-and-manga-list/.167197|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="2021YearinReview">{{Cite web|last=Peters|first=Megan|title=My Hero Academia Is Dominating Tumblr's Anime Year in Review|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/news/anime-manga-year-in-review-2021-tumblr/|website=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=December 2, 2021|access-date=February 29, 2024|archive-date=September 27, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927004320/https://comicbook.com/anime/news/anime-manga-year-in-review-2021-tumblr/|url-status=live}}</ref> The characters also placed highly in the rankings of the Top Anime & Manga Characters category. In 2019, Izuku Midoriya ranked first, with 17 other spots being occupied by other ''My Hero Academia'' characters in the top 50 list;<ref name="2019YearinReview"/> seven were ranked on the top 10 list in 2020;<ref name="2020YearinReview"/> and five in 2021.<ref name="2021YearinReview"/> The series also ranked fifth on Tumblr's Top 10 overall in the 2018 list;<ref>{{Cite web|author=J. K|title=Here Are The Top K-Pop Stars And More On Tumblr In 2018|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1271379wpp/top-k-pop-stars-tumblr-2018|publisher=[[Soompi]]|date=November 30, 2018|access-date=February 29, 2024|archive-date=December 3, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203035638/https://www.soompi.com/article/1271379wpp/top-k-pop-stars-tumblr-2018|url-status=live}}</ref> it ranked ninth on the Top 20 overall in 2020;<ref name="2020YearinReview"/> and tenth on the Top 21 overall in 2021.<ref name="2021YearinReview"/> It placed seventeenth on Twitter Japan's Trend Awards in 2021, based on the social network's top [[Twitter trends|trending topics]] of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Harding|first=Daryl|title=Chainsaw Man Trends Higher Than Evangelion, JUJUTSU KAISEN on Twitter Japan in 2021|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2021/12/21-1/chainsaw-man-trends-higher-than-evangelion-jujutsu-kaisen-on-twitter-japan-in-2021|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=December 21, 2021|access-date=December 21, 2021|archive-date=December 21, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221101316/https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2021/12/21-1/chainsaw-man-trends-higher-than-evangelion-jujutsu-kaisen-on-twitter-japan-in-2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

In April 2024, ''My Hero Academia'' was the most popular animated superhero show or franchise according to analyst Miles Atherton, where the data was compiled through social media engagement for the popular new series and its growing popularity for anime. With 4.7 million social media engagements, it was the second most-discussed series, ahead of ''[[X-Men '97]]'', ''[[Invincible (TV series)|Invincible]]'', and ''[[KonoSuba]]'' in the last 30 days, despite the [[My Hero Academia season 7|seventh season]] having not began airing.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Peters|first=Megan|title=My Hero Academia Usurps X-Men '97, Star Wars Chatter Online|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-anime-social-media-xmen-star-wars/|website=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=April 20, 2024|access-date=April 23, 2024|archive-date=April 22, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240422102929/https://comicbook.com/anime/news/my-hero-academia-anime-social-media-xmen-star-wars/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Manga ===
==== Sales ====
''My Hero Academia'' has been a significant commercial success since the manga's release; in 2014, the first volume reached seventh place on [[Oricon]]'s weekly manga chart with 71,575 copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, November 3–9|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-12/japanese-comic-ranking-november-3-9/.80954|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 12, 2014|access-date=November 30, 2014|archive-date=December 2, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141202185018/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-12/japanese-comic-ranking-november-3-9/.80954|url-status=live}}</ref> It sold out almost immediately on its first printing.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:マンガ質問状 ： 「僕のヒーローアカデミア」　コミックス1巻即完売のアツい「ジャンプ」新鋭|url=http://mantan-web.jp/2014/12/01/20141130dog00m200046000c.html|website=[[Mantan Web]]|date=December 1, 2014|access-date=December 4, 2014|language=ja|archive-date=December 7, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207224731/http://mantan-web.jp/2014/12/01/20141130dog00m200046000c.html?mode=pc|url-status=dead}}</ref> Volume two reached sixth place, with 167,531 copies<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:週間 コミックランキング 2015年01月19日付|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/obc/w/2015-01-19/|website=[[Oricon Style]]|publisher=[[Oricon]]|access-date=January 20, 2015|language=ja|archive-date=January 19, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150119223440/http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/obc/w/2015-01-19/|url-status=dead}}</ref> and, by January 18, 2015, had sold 205,179 copies.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, January 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-01-21/japanese-comic-ranking-january-12-18/.83552|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 21, 2015|access-date=January 22, 2015|archive-date=January 22, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150122012934/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-01-21/japanese-comic-ranking-january-12-18/.83552|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2015, volume three reached eighth place with 254,111 copies.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, November 3–9|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-12/japanese-comic-ranking-november-3-9/.80954|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 12, 2014|access-date=March 20, 2021|archive-date=July 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723181905/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-12/japanese-comic-ranking-november-3-9/.80954|url-status=live}}</ref> Volume four reached sixth with 259,137 in June,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, June 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-06-24/japanese-comic-ranking-june-15-21/.89666|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 24, 2015|access-date=March 20, 2021|archive-date=June 27, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627112249/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-06-24/japanese-comic-ranking-june-15-21/.89666|url-status=live}}</ref> and volume five peaked at ninth place with 279,414 copies in August.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, August 17–23|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-08-26/japanese-comic-ranking-august-17-23/.92166|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 26, 2015|access-date=March 20, 2021|archive-date=January 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125012241/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-08-26/japanese-comic-ranking-august-17-23/.92166|url-status=live}}</ref>

By March 2017, the manga had over 10 million copies in circulation;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|title=My Hero Academia Has Over 10 Million Copies in Print|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2017-03-31/my-hero-academia-has-over-10-million-copies-in-print/.114078|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 31, 2017|access-date=March 31, 2017|archive-date=March 31, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170331151059/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2017-03-31/my-hero-academia-has-over-10-million-copies-in-print/.114078|url-status=live}}</ref> over 13 million copies in circulation by February 2018;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Manga Has 13 Million Copies in Print|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2018-02-03/my-hero-academia-manga-has-13-million-copies-in-print/.127332|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 3, 2018|access-date=February 4, 2018|archive-date=November 10, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211110000846/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2018-02-03/my-hero-academia-manga-has-13-million-copies-in-print/.127332|url-status=live}}</ref> over 15 million copies in circulation by May 2018;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=Roundup of Newly Revealed Print Counts for Manga, Light Novel Series (May–June 2018)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-06-09/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series/.132368|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 9, 2018|access-date=June 10, 2018|archive-date=July 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705195428/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-06-09/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series/.132368|url-status=live}}</ref> over 16 million copies in circulation by August 2018;<ref>{{Cite news|last=Valdez|first=Nick|title='My Hero Academia' Hits Big New Sales Milestone|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/2018/08/07/my-hero-academia-manga-new-sales-milestone-16-million/|website=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=August 7, 2018|access-date=October 22, 2018|archive-date=October 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181022153310/https://comicbook.com/anime/2018/08/07/my-hero-academia-manga-new-sales-milestone-16-million/|url-status=live}}</ref> over 17 million copies in circulation by September 2018;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=Roundup of Newly Revealed Print Counts for Manga, Light Novel Series (September) – Updated|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-29/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series-updated/.136106|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 29, 2018|access-date=September 30, 2018|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612032942/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-29/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series-updated/.136106|url-status=live}}</ref> over 20 million copies in circulation by December 2018;<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:「僕のヒーローアカデミア」新キャラ登場の第4期PVを公開！放送は2019年10月スタート!!|url=https://thetv.jp/news/detail/173867/|website=The Television|publisher=[[Kadokawa Corporation]]|date=December 23, 2018|access-date=December 24, 2018|language=ja|archive-date=December 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224220132/https://thetv.jp/news/detail/173867/|url-status=live}}</ref> over 21 million copies in circulation by February 2019;<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Sherman|first1=Jennifer|last2=Ressler|first2=Karen|last3=Hodgkins|first3=Crystalyn|title=Roundup of Newly Revealed Print Counts for Manga, Light Novel Series – February 2019 (Updated)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-03/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series-february-2019/.143286|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 3, 2019|access-date=March 4, 2019|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612032944/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-03/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series-february-2019/.143286|url-status=live}}</ref> over 26 million copies in circulation by December 2019;<ref>{{Cite press release|script-title=ja:12月20日公開『僕のヒーローアカデミア THE MOVIE ヒーローズ：ライジング』入場者に『ヒロバト』の限定カード「ホークス」をプレゼント！本日ビジュアル初公開！|url=http://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000116.000009185.html|publisher=[[Takara Tomy Arts]]|via=[[PR Times]]|date=December 6, 2019|access-date=December 6, 2019|language=ja|archive-date=December 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206050526/https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000116.000009185.html|url-status=live}}</ref> over 30 million copies in circulation by January 2021;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|title=My Hero Academia Manga Has Over 30 Million Copies in Circulation|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-01-03/my-hero-academia-manga-has-over-30-million-copies-in-circulation/.168089|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 3, 2021|access-date=January 4, 2021|archive-date=January 4, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104030836/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-01-03/my-hero-academia-manga-has-over-30-million-copies-in-circulation/.168089|url-status=live}}</ref> over 50 million copies in circulation by April 2021, with 37 million being sold in Japan and the remaining 13 million in the rest of the world;<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:僕のヒーローアカデミア：コミックス全世界累計5000万部突破 特設サイトにデクの激動の1年 荼毘の電波ジャックも|url=https://mantan-web.jp/article/20210401dog00m200054000c.html|website=[[Mantan Web]]|date=April 2, 2021|access-date=April 2, 2021|language=ja|archive-date=May 1, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501234032/https://mantan-web.jp/article/20210401dog00m200054000c.html|url-status=live}}</ref> over 65 million copies in circulation by January 2022,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=My Hero Academia Manga Tops 65 Million Copies in Circulation Worldwide|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-01-30/my-hero-academia-manga-tops-65-million-copies-in-circulation-worldwide/.182034|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 30, 2022|access-date=January 30, 2022|archive-date=January 30, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220130122938/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-01-30/my-hero-academia-manga-tops-65-million-copies-in-circulation-worldwide/.182034|url-status=live}}</ref> with 45 million being sold in Japan and the remaining 20 million elsewhere;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Frater|first=Patrick|title='Bleach,' 'My Hero Academia' Special Editions to Be Launched by Viz Media|url=https://variety.com/2022/global/asia/bleach-my-hero-academia-special-editions-1235226202/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 7, 2022|access-date=April 20, 2022|archive-date=April 20, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420170558/https://variety.com/2022/global/asia/bleach-my-hero-academia-special-editions-1235226202/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="10M Copies">{{Cite web|last=Hazra|first=Adriana|title=Bleach Manga Crosses 2.7 Million Copies in Print in U.S., My Hero Academia Manga Crosses 10 Million|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-04-19/bleach-manga-crosses-2.7-million-copies-in-print-in-u.s-my-hero-academia-manga-crosses-10-million/.184723|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 19, 2022|access-date=April 20, 2022|archive-date=April 20, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420171910/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-04-19/bleach-manga-crosses-2.7-million-copies-in-print-in-u.s-my-hero-academia-manga-crosses-10-million/.184723|url-status=live}}</ref> over 85 million copies in circulation by February 2023;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=My Hero Academia Tops 85 Million Copies in Circulation Worldwide|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-02-03/my-hero-academia-tops-85-million-copies-in-circulation-worldwide/.194510|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 3, 2023|access-date=February 3, 2023|archive-date=February 3, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203231258/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-02-03/my-hero-academia-tops-85-million-copies-in-circulation-worldwide/.194510|url-status=live}}</ref> and over 100 million copies in circulation by April 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:「僕のヒーローアカデミア」発行部数が1億部突破、堀越耕平の描き下ろしイラスト到着|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/567890|website=[[Comic Natalie]]|publisher=Natasha, Inc.|date=April 4, 2024|access-date=April 3, 2024|language=ja|archive-date=April 3, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240403153941/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/567890|url-status=live}}</ref>{{Efn|Including the number of spin-off manga}}

The ''My Hero Academia'' franchise sales generated an estimated ¥16 billion in revenue in Japan between 2016 and 2020.<ref>Physical media franchise sales:
