*2019 physical media franchise sales{{Citation needed|date=April 2024}} referring to:
* {{Cite web|url=http://yaraon-blog.com/archives/187807?s=2020|title=sales by comprehensive series|website=Yaraon|date=December 25, 2020|access-date=March 21, 2022|language=ja|archive-date=March 27, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327234059/http://yaraon-blog.com/archives/187807?s=2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The series was the sixth best-selling manga series in the first half of 2017, with over 2 million copies sold,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2017 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2017/.116861|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 1, 2017|access-date=June 2, 2017|archive-date=April 13, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220413132115/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2017/.116861|url-status=live}}</ref> while volumes 12 and 13 were some of the top 50 best-selling manga volumes.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2017 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2017/.116863|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 1, 2017|access-date=June 2, 2017|archive-date=May 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220508152008/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2017/.116863|url-status=live}}</ref> By the end of the year, it was the fourth best-selling manga series with over 5.8 million copies sold,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2017|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-06/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2017/.124894|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 6, 2017|access-date=December 7, 2017|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612201732/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-06/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2017/.124894|url-status=live}}</ref> while volumes 12–15 were among the 50 best-selling manga volumes.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2017|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-06/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2017/.124895|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 6, 2017|access-date=December 7, 2017|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612033053/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-06/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2017/.124895|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018, the seventeenth volume of the manga had received an initial print run of 600,000 copies.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ressler|first=Karen|title=Manga With Biggest 1st Printings from Kodansha, Shogakukan, Shueisha: 2017–2018|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-06/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2017-2018/.130071|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 6, 2018|access-date=May 6, 2018|archive-date=November 9, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109020624/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-06/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2017-2018/.130071|url-status=live}}</ref> It was the fifth best-selling manga in the first half of 2018 with over 2.5 million copies sold,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2018 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-05-31/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2018/.132243|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 31, 2018|access-date=June 1, 2018|archive-date=April 9, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409000734/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-05-31/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2018/.132243|url-status=live}}</ref> while volumes 17 and 18 were the thirteenth and seventeenth best-selling manga volumes, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2018 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-05-31/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2018/.132245|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 31, 2018|access-date=June 1, 2018|archive-date=September 12, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210912022443/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-05-31/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2018/.132245|url-status=live}}</ref> The series ranked sixth on [[Rakuten]]'s Top 20 Best Selling Digital Manga of 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:2018年間ランキング 総合＆ジャンル別（小説・ライトノベル・ビジネス・BLコミック）|url=https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/2018/11/ranking-yearly/|website=[[Rakuten]]|date=November 26, 2018|access-date=November 26, 2022|language=ja|archive-date=November 26, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221126050135/https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/2018/11/ranking-yearly/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was the second best-selling manga of 2018, behind ''One Piece'', with over 6.7 million copies sold;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2018|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2018/.140163|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 30, 2018|access-date=December 1, 2018|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612033100/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2018/.140163|url-status=live}}</ref> volumes 17–20 were among the 50 best-selling manga volumes, having sold over 3 million copies combined.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2018|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2018/.140164|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 30, 2018|access-date=December 1, 2018|archive-date=May 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512134324/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2018/.140164|url-status=live}}</ref> The 22nd volume topped Oricon's ranking sales chart list in February 2019, with 576,148 copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Comics in Japan: February 2019|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-26/top-selling-comics-in-japan-february-2019/.144808|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 26, 2019|access-date=March 27, 2019|archive-date=May 11, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220511064324/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-26/top-selling-comics-in-japan-february-2019/.144808|url-status=live}}</ref> The series was the fourth best-selling manga in the first half of 2019, with over 3.1 million copies sold;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2019 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-05-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2019/.147237|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 29, 2019|access-date=May 30, 2019|archive-date=April 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220405092115/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-05-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2019/.147237|url-status=live}}</ref> volumes 21–23 were among the 50 best-selling manga volumes of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2019 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-05-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2019/.147238|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 29, 2019|access-date=May 30, 2019|archive-date=May 28, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220528031854/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-05-29/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2019/.147238|url-status=live}}</ref> It was the sixth best-selling manga in 2019, with over 5 million copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2019|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-27/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2019/.153758|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 27, 2019|access-date=November 28, 2019|archive-date=February 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225022136/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-27/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2019/.153758|url-status=live}}</ref> Along with ''[[One-Punch Man]]'', the series had an initial print run of 660,000 copies, with its 26th volume in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=Manga With Biggest 1st Printings from Kodansha, Shogakukan, Shueisha: 2019–2020|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-04-04/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2019-2020/.158303|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 5, 2020|access-date=May 6, 2020|archive-date=May 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200513223411/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-04-04/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2019-2020/.158303|url-status=live}}</ref> The series was the fifth best-selling manga in the first half of 2020, with over 3 million copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2020 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-05-28/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2020/.159991|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 28, 2020|access-date=May 29, 2020|archive-date=June 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612033014/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-05-28/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2020/.159991|url-status=live}}</ref> It ranked twelfth on Rakuten's Top 20 Best Selling Digital Manga of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:楽天Kobo電子書籍ストア2020年間ランキング 総合・小説・ライトノベル・ビジネス・BLコミック|url=https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/2020/11/ranking-yearly/|website=[[Rakuten]]|date=November 25, 2020|access-date=November 26, 2022|language=ja|archive-date=November 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221101072925/https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/2020/11/ranking-yearly/|url-status=live}}</ref>

''My Hero Academia'' was the eighth best-selling manga series in 2020, with over 6 million copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:2020年度 オリコン年間“本”ランキング【コミック作品別】TOP10|url=https://music.oricon.co.jp/php/special/Special.php?pcd=book_nenkan20_work&site=book|website=[[Oricon ME inc.|Oricon ME Inc.]]|publisher=[[Oricon]]|access-date=January 8, 2021|language=ja|archive-date=January 8, 2021|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210108120514/https://music.oricon.co.jp/php/special/Special.php?pcd=book_nenkan20_work&site=book|url-status=dead}}</ref> The 29th volume had an initial print run of 680,000 copies in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=Manga With Biggest 1st Printings from Kodansha, Shogakukan, Shueisha: 2020–2021|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-04-08/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2020-2021/.171563|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 9, 2021|access-date=May 6, 2021|archive-date=April 22, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422084036/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-04-08/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2020-2021/.171563|url-status=live}}</ref> The series was the fifth best-selling manga in 2021 and 2022, with over 7 million and 5.3 million copies sold, respectively;<ref>Oricon's best-selling manga series:
* {{Cite web|script-title=ja:コミック作品別ランキング1～5位|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/special/57840/5/|website=[[Oricon News]]|publisher=[[Oricon]]|date=November 29, 2021|access-date=November 28, 2021|language=ja|archive-date=November 28, 2021|archive-url=https://archive.today/20211128195527/https://www.oricon.co.jp/special/57840/5/|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2022 — Jujutsu Kaisen Edges Out Tokyo Revengers|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-12-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2022-jujutsu-kaisen-edges-out-tokyo-revengers/.192470|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 2, 2022|access-date=December 2, 2022|archive-date=December 2, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221202100641/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-12-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2022-jujutsu-kaisen-edges-out-tokyo-revengers/.192470|url-status=live}}</ref> volumes 33–35 were among the 30 best-selling manga volumes of 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2022 — Jujutsu Kaisen 18 Sells 2.11 Million|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-12-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2022-jujutsu-kaisen-18-sells-2.11-million/.192471|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 2, 2022|access-date=December 2, 2022|archive-date=December 2, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221202100744/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-12-01/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2022-jujutsu-kaisen-18-sells-2.11-million/.192471|url-status=live}}</ref> It ranked eighth on Rakuten's Top 20 Best Selling Digital Manga of 2021, and ninth in 2022.<ref>Rakuten's Top 20 Best Selling Digital Manga:
* {{Cite web|script-title=ja:楽天Kobo2021年間ランキング 総合・小説・ライトノベル・ビジネス・BLコミック|url=https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/ranking-yearly/archives/2021/|website=[[Rakuten]]|date=November 29, 2021|access-date=November 26, 2022|language=ja|archive-date=November 26, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221126050136/https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/ranking-yearly/archives/2021/|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|script-title=ja:楽天Kobo2022年間ランキング 総合・小説・ライトノベル・ビジネス・BLコミック|url=https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/ranking-yearly/archives/2022/|website=[[Rakuten]]|date=November 24, 2022|access-date=November 26, 2022|language=ja|archive-date=February 20, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240220023306/https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/ranking-yearly/archives/2022/|url-status=live}}</ref> Volumes 37–39 were among the best-selling manga volumes of 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Volume: 2023 — One Piece Tops Chart for 13th Time|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-11-30/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2023-one-piece-tops-chart-for-13th-time/.204968|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 30, 2023|access-date=November 30, 2023|archive-date=November 30, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130063153/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-11-30/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-volume-2023-one-piece-tops-chart-for-13th-time/.204968|url-status=live}}</ref> The series ranked twelfth on Rakuten's Top 20 Best Selling Digital Manga of 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:楽天Kobo2023年間ランキング 総合・小説・ライトノベル・ビジネス・BL|url=https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/ranking-yearly/|website=[[Rakuten]]|date=December 30, 2023|access-date=February 19, 2024|language=ja|archive-date=November 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221101072926/https://books.rakuten.co.jp/e-book/article/ranking-yearly/|url-status=live}}</ref> Volume 38 was [[Shueisha]]'s fifth-highest first print run manga volume of 2023–2024 (period from April 2023 to March 2024), with 815,000 copies printed.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|title=Manga With Biggest 1st Printings from Kodansha, Shogakukan, Shueisha: 2023–2024|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2024-04-07/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2023-2024/.209605|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 7, 2024|access-date=April 7, 2024|archive-date=April 7, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240407173159/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2024-04-07/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2023-2024/.209605|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2024, the 42nd and final volume sold 1 million copies in its first week, making ''My Hero Academia'' the fourth manga series to achieve this feat in a single print volume, with the others being ''Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba'', ''Attack on Titan'', and ''One Piece''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=De Souza|first=Merlyn|title=My Hero Academia's Final Volume Makes History Breaking an Incredible Sales Record|url=https://screenrant.com/mha-hero-academia-volume-42-sales-record/|website=[[Screen Rant]]|date=December 11, 2024|access-date=December 16, 2024|archive-date=December 16, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241216061039/https://screenrant.com/mha-hero-academia-volume-42-sales-record/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was also the series' highest-selling manga volume in  Oricon's first week chart, with 616,671 copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:週間 コミックランキング 2024年12月16日付|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/obc/w/2024-12-16/|website=[[Oricon Style]]|publisher=[[Oricon]]|access-date=December 16, 2024|language=ja|archive-date=December 13, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213112508/https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/obc/w/2024-12-16/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Its volume had an initial print run of 850,000 copies printed, making it Shueisha's sixth-highest first print run manga volume of 2024–2025 (period from April 2024 to March 2025).<ref>{{Cite web|last=Cayanan|first=Joanna|title=Manga With Biggest 1st Printings from Kodansha, Shogakukan, Shueisha: 2024-2025|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2025-04-07/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2024-2025/.223292|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 7, 2025|access-date=April 8, 2025|archive-date=April 7, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250407132738/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2025-04-07/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2024-2025/.223292|url-status=live}}</ref>

