According to ''ICv2'', ''My Hero Academia'' was the fifth best-selling manga franchise in Q4 2021 (September–December) in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=ICv2 Lists Top-Selling Manga Franchises for Fall 2021 According to NPD Bookscan Sales Reports|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-03-02/icv2-lists-top-selling-manga-franchises-for-fall-2021-according-to-npd-bookscan-sales-reports/.183180|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 2, 2022|access-date=March 2, 2022|archive-date=March 2, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220302220919/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-03-02/icv2-lists-top-selling-manga-franchises-for-fall-2021-according-to-npd-bookscan-sales-reports/.183180|url-status=live}}</ref> According to NPD BookScan, it was the best-selling manga series in 2020, with nine volumes featured on the top 20 adult graphic novels list;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hazra|first=Adriana|title=My Hero Academia Ranks at #1 on U.S. Annual BookScan 2020 List|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-01-24/my-hero-academia-ranks-at-no.1-on-u.s-annual-bookscan-2020-list/.168720|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 24, 2021|access-date=August 3, 2022|archive-date=March 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308130909/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2021-01-24/my-hero-academia-ranks-at-no.1-on-u.s-annual-bookscan-2020-list/.168720|url-status=live}}</ref> seven volumes were ranked among the top 20 highest-selling manga volumes in 2021;<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mateo|first=Alex|title=ICv2 Lists Top-Selling Manga Volumes for 2021 According to NPD Bookscan Sales Reports|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-03-04/icv2-lists-top-selling-manga-volumes-for-2021-according-to-npd-bookscan-sales-reports/.183258|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 4, 2022|access-date=March 5, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305013608/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2022-03-04/icv2-lists-top-selling-manga-volumes-for-2021-according-to-npd-bookscan-sales-reports/.183258|url-status=live}}</ref> two volumes were among the top 20 highest-selling manga volumes in 2022 and 2023.<ref>NPD BookScan's Top-Selling Manga Volumes of 2022 and 2023:
* {{Cite web|last=Hazra|first=Adriana|title=Chainsaw Man Ranks #1 on NPD Bookscan's Top-Selling Manga of 2022 List|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-03-05/chainsaw-man-ranks-no.1-on-npd-bookscan-top-selling-manga-of-2022-list/.195600|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 5, 2023|access-date=March 5, 2023|archive-date=March 5, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230305211845/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-03-05/chainsaw-man-ranks-no.1-on-npd-bookscan-top-selling-manga-of-2022-list/.195600|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Hazra|first=Adriana|title=ICv2 Lists Top-Selling Manga Volumes for 2023 According to Circana BookScan Sales Reports|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2024-02-03/icv2-lists-top-selling-manga-volumes-for-2023-according-to-circana-bookscan-sales-reports/.207146|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 3, 2024|access-date=February 4, 2024|archive-date=February 3, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240203154607/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2024-02-03/icv2-lists-top-selling-manga-volumes-for-2023-according-to-circana-bookscan-sales-reports/.207146|url-status=live}}</ref> The first volume had over 1.2 million copies in circulation by 2022 and the franchise as a whole has over 10 million copies in circulation in the United States.<ref name="10M Copies"/>

==== Critical reception ====
Nick Creamer of [[Anime News Network]] gave the first volume a B rating. Creamer praised Horikoshi's artwork, describing it as "absolutely professional" and "consistent and highly polished", but also stated that it was fast-paced and very sharply drawn. He praised the plot and characters, saying that despite it feeling like a typical ''shōnen'' plot, it did well enough to still feel fresh and entertaining. He also stated that the characters had great energy and personality.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Creamer|first=Nick|title=My Hero Academia GN 1 – Review|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia/gn-1/.92436|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 6, 2015|access-date=May 13, 2020|archive-date=December 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211031431/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia/gn-1/.92436|url-status=live}}</ref> Isaac Akers from ''The Fandom Post'' gave the second volume a B+ rating. He praised the art, saying that Horikoshi's character designs and art bolster the volume's ability to feel as if it does everything it does just because the volume likes doing it. He concluded that ''My Hero Academia'' was a difficult series to dislike, making it as the "real joy to read" by executing the author's ideas and having enough nerve and twist.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Akers|first=Isaac|title=My Hero Academia Vol. #02 Manga Review|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2015/11/28/my-hero-academia-vol-02-manga-review/|website=The Fandom Post|date=November 28, 2015|access-date=April 3, 2021|archive-date=July 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711033428/http://www.fandompost.com/2015/11/28/my-hero-academia-vol-02-manga-review/|url-status=live}}</ref> Sean Gaffney from ''A Case Suitable for Treatment'' referred to the art as "smooth" and complemented how it flows with the action. Gaffney also praised the story, characters, and fight scenes, stating that the story flows nicely with each of their individual personalities, while the fight scenes look smooth and non-confusing.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Gaffney|first=Sean|title=My Hero Academia, Vol. 1|url=http://suitablefortreatment.mangabookshelf.com/2015/08/11/my-hero-academia-vol-1/|website=A Case Suitable for Treatment|date=August 11, 2015|access-date=April 3, 2021|archive-date=June 8, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160608212341/http://suitablefortreatment.mangabookshelf.com/2015/08/11/my-hero-academia-vol-1/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In a review of the second volume, Leroy Douresseaux from ''Comic Book Bin'' also praised the story, specifically the way it executed comedy and drama. He also compared the series to the other superhero works such as ''[[Tiger & Bunny]]'' and ''One-Punch Man'', stating that ''My Hero Academia'' proved that "manga can do superhero comic books that are every bit as imaginative as American superhero comics".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Douresseaux|first=Leroy|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/myheroacademia002.html|title=My Hero Academia: Volume 2 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|date=November 17, 2015|access-date=April 6, 2021|archive-date=May 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508212712/http://www.comicbookbin.com/myheroacademia002.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Manga Bookshelf praised the first volume for its art, saying that it demonstrated Horikoshi's skill very well, though criticizing it for having too much narration at some points.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manga-news.com/index.php/manga/critique/My-Hero-Academia/vol-1|title=My Hero Academia Vol.1 Izuku Midoriya: les origines Critique du volume manga|website=Manga News|date=June 8, 2016|access-date=April 6, 2021|language=fr|archive-date=November 14, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114151951/http://www.manga-news.com/index.php/manga/critique/My-Hero-Academia/vol-1|url-status=live}}</ref> Reviewing volumes 1 to 19, Michelle Smith from ''Soliloquy in Blue'' called the plot "very good", but also stated that the main reason she liked the series was the characters, specifically praising most of the main cast. However, she criticized the series for not giving some of the female characters enough spotlight despite praising their varied character designs and personalities.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Smith|first=Michelle|url=http://soliloquyinblue.mangabookshelf.com/2019/06/27/my-hero-academia-vols-1-19/|title=My Hero Academia, Vols. 1–19|website=Soliloquy in Blue|date=June 27, 2019|access-date=April 6, 2021|archive-date=February 19, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219082842/http://soliloquyinblue.mangabookshelf.com/2019/06/27/my-hero-academia-vols-1-19/|url-status=live}}</ref>

The series was chosen as one of the Best Manga at the [[Comic-Con International]] Best & Worst Manga in 2018 and 2019.<ref>Comic-Con International Best & Worst Manga:
* {{Cite web|last=Loveridge|first=Lynzee|title=Best and Worst Manga of 2018 Results – Comic-Con International|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2018-07-24/best-and-worst-manga-of-2018-results-comic-con-international/.134599|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 24, 2018|access-date=April 1, 2022|archive-date=November 9, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109102145/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2018-07-24/best-and-worst-manga-of-2018-results-comic-con-international/.134599|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|last=Loveridge|first=Lynzee|title=Best and Worst Manga of 2019 Results – Comic-Con International|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-07-22/best-and-worst-manga-of-2019-results-comic-con-international/.149230|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 22, 2019|access-date=April 1, 2022|archive-date=April 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220401101450/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-07-22/best-and-worst-manga-of-2019-results-comic-con-international/.149230|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Barnes & Noble]] named it on their list of "Our Favorite Manga of 2018", saying that "it combines the earnestness of superhero comics with the core elements of shonen manga", but also stated that the reason the story was a delight was due to Horikoshi's "endlessly inventive imagination", praising most of the characters' abilities that are more "quirks" than superpowers.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Alverson|first=Brigid|title=Our Favorite Manga of 2018|url=https://www.barnesandnoble.com/blog/sci-fi-fantasy/best-manga-of-2018/|website=[[Barnes & Noble]]|date=December 20, 2018|access-date=June 26, 2020|archive-date=December 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181221081410/https://www.barnesandnoble.com/blog/sci-fi-fantasy/best-manga-of-2018/|url-status=live}}</ref> Cold Cobra of ''Anime UK News'' picked the series for his list of "best manga of 2010s", praising its mix between the Japanese shonen action genre and American superhero comics. He stated that its cast of characters is what makes it stand out more than anything. He described the artwork as "wonderfully expressive and occasionally impressively shaded for those big full-page moments", which made it a joy to read.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Anime and Manga of the Decade 2010–2019 – Anime UK News Writers' Top Picks!|url=https://animeuknews.net/2019/12/anime-and-manga-of-the-decade-2010-2019-anime-uk-news-writers-top-picks/|website=Anime UK News|date=December 23, 2019|access-date=December 24, 2019|archive-date=December 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224053101/https://animeuknews.net/2019/12/anime-and-manga-of-the-decade-2010-2019-anime-uk-news-writers-top-picks/|url-status=live}}</ref>

