=== Anime ===
==== Sales ====
''My Hero Academia'' sales have been high and the series has been successful in Japan since the release of the anime. The five volumes of the [[My Hero Academia season 1|first season]] on [[Blu-ray]] and DVD were released in Japan, with each release appearing in Oricon's Animation Blu-ray and Animation DVD ranking. The first Blu-ray edition of ''My Hero Academia'' ranked fifth in the first week of Oricon's Blu-ray ranking, while the first DVD edition ranked fourth with 2,184 copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, June 27 – July 3|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-05/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-june-27-july-3/.104005|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 5, 2016|access-date=July 5, 2016|archive-date=July 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704224346/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-05/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-june-27-july-3/.104005|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, June 27 – July 3|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-05/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-june-27-july-3/.104006|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 5, 2016|access-date=July 5, 2016|archive-date=January 31, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220131200836/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-05/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-june-27-july-3/.104006|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The second Blu-ray and DVD sets also ranked, with the Blu-ray edition coming in sixth and DVD fifth for a week.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, July 11–17|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-19/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-july-11-17/.104465|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 19, 2016|access-date=July 19, 2016|archive-date=January 3, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220103184915/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-19/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-july-11-17/.104465|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, July 11–17|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-19/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-july-11-17/.104466|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 19, 2016|access-date=July 19, 2016|archive-date=May 9, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220509051233/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-19/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-july-11-17/.104466|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The third Blu-ray edition ranked fourth with 1,700 copies sold, while the DVD release was eighth with 1,184 copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, August 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-23/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-august-15-21/.105678|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 23, 2016|access-date=August 23, 2016|archive-date=March 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308134254/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-23/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-august-15-21/.105678|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, August 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-23/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-august-15-21/.105679|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 23, 2016|access-date=August 23, 2016|archive-date=July 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705004308/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-23/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-august-15-21/.105679|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The fourth Blu-ray and DVD collections ranked fifth and fourth, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, September 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-20/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-september-12-18/.106672|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 20, 2016|access-date=September 20, 2016|archive-date=December 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218015409/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-20/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-september-12-18/.106672|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, September 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-20/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-september-12-18/.106673|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 20, 2016|access-date=September 20, 2016|archive-date=July 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704212555/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-20/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-september-12-18/.106673|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The fifth Blu-ray and DVD release sales ranked higher than the previous volumes; the Blu-ray came in at third with 1,473 copies sold and the DVD ranked second with 1,068 copies sold in a week.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, October 10–16|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-18/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-october-10-16/.107793|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 18, 2016|access-date=October 18, 2016|archive-date=January 21, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121211500/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-18/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-october-10-16/.107793|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, October 10–16|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-18/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-october-10-16/.107794|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 18, 2016|access-date=October 18, 2016|archive-date=January 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125180018/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-18/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-october-10-16/.107794|url-status=live}}</p></ref> Four volumes of the second season on Blu-ray and DVD also appeared in Oricon's Animation Blu-ray and DVD ranking. The first Blu-ray edition ranked seventh, while the DVD ranked fifth.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, July 17–23|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-26/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-july-17-23/.119329|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 26, 2017|access-date=July 26, 2017|archive-date=July 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705021942/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-26/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-july-17-23/.119329|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, July 17–23|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-26/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-july-17-23/.119331|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 26, 2017|access-date=July 26, 2017|archive-date=July 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704223058/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-26/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-july-17-23/.119331|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The third Blu-ray edition was among the top 20 in Oricon's Animation Blu-ray ranking, while the DVD was tenth among the 30 Animation DVD ranking.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, September 11–17|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-19/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-september-11-17/.121552|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 19, 2017|access-date=September 19, 2017|archive-date=July 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705011915/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-19/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-september-11-17/.121552|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, September 11–17|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-19/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-september-11-17/.121557|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 19, 2017|access-date=September 19, 2017|archive-date=July 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220706192400/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-19/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-september-11-17/.121557|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The seventh Blu-ray and DVD ranked eighth,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, January 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-01-23/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-january-15-21/.126806|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 23, 2018|access-date=January 23, 2018|archive-date=March 2, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220302233905/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-01-23/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-january-15-21/.126806|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, January 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-01-23/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-january-15-21/.126807|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 23, 2018|access-date=January 23, 2018|archive-date=April 22, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220422142307/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-01-23/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-january-15-21/.126807|url-status=live}}</p></ref> while the eighth Blu-ray and DVD sets ranked fourth.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, February 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-02-20/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-february-12-18/.128031|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 20, 2018|access-date=February 20, 2018|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304115610/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-02-20/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-february-12-18/.128031|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, February 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-02-20/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-february-12-18/.128032|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 20, 2018|access-date=February 20, 2018|archive-date=March 3, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303221221/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-02-20/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-february-12-18/.128032|url-status=live}}</p></ref>

The second season's opening theme, "Peace Sign" by Kenshi Yonezu, topped the [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'' charts]] on the [[Billboard Japan Hot 100]];<ref>{{Cite web|title=Hot 100|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100&year=2017&month=07&day=03|magazine=[[Billboard Japan]]|access-date=June 29, 2017|language=ja|archive-date=July 19, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719224511/https://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100&year=2017&month=07&day=03|url-status=live}}</ref> it peaked at number two on the [[Oricon Singles Chart|Oricon charts]].<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ja:ピースサイン(ピース盤/初回限定盤)|trans-title=Peace Sign (Peace Edition/First Press Limited Edition)|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/560188/products/1235559/1/|website=[[Oricon News]]|publisher=[[Oricon]]|access-date=July 22, 2017|language=ja|archive-date=September 30, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230930095409/https://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/560188/products/1235559/1/|url-status=live}}</ref> By the end of 2017, the ''[[Bootleg (Kenshi Yonezu album)|Bootleg]]'' soundtrack album including "Peace Sign" became the top-selling anime CD album on Oricon's chart with 241,754 copies sold.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Anime CD Albums: 2017|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-23/top-selling-anime-cd-albums-2017/.125685|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 23, 2017|access-date=December 23, 2017|archive-date=April 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220406153524/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-23/top-selling-anime-cd-albums-2017/.125685|url-status=live}}</ref> It was the top-selling anime CD album in the first half of 2018 with 134,777 copies sold; the other compilation album, ''LiSA BEST: Day'', which includes the second ending theme song of the second season, "Datte Atashi no Hero" by [[Lisa (Japanese musician, born 1987)|LiSA]], ranked fifth on Oricon's chart simultaneously.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Anime CD Albums: 2018 (First Half)|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-06-26/top-selling-anime-cd-albums-2018/.133439|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 26, 2018|access-date=June 26, 2018|archive-date=August 6, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210806044005/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-06-26/top-selling-anime-cd-albums-2018/.133439|url-status=live}}</ref> Seven volumes of the [[My Hero Academia season 3|third season]] on Blu-ray and DVD appeared in Oricon's Animation Blu-ray and DVD ranking, respectively. The first Blu-ray edition ranked ninth, while the DVD ranked third.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, July 16–22|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-07-24/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-july-16-22/.134630|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 24, 2018|access-date=July 24, 2018|archive-date=December 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210012523/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-07-24/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-july-16-22/.134630|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, July 16–22|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-07-24/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-july-16-22/.134632|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 24, 2018|access-date=July 24, 2018|archive-date=October 27, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211027101028/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-07-24/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-july-16-22/.134632|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The second Blu-ray edition ranked sixth, while the DVD ranked fifth.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, August 13–19|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-21/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-august-13-19/.135720|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 21, 2018|access-date=August 21, 2018|archive-date=December 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210012514/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-21/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-august-13-19/.135720|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, August 13–19|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-21/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-august-13-19/.135722|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 21, 2018|access-date=August 21, 2018|archive-date=May 23, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220523031648/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-21/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-august-13-19/.135722|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The third Blu-ray edition ranked fourth, while the DVD ranked second.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, September 17–23|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-25/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-september-17-23/.137277|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 25, 2018|access-date=September 25, 2018|archive-date=December 1, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211201042936/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-25/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-september-17-23/.137277|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, September 17–23|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-25/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-september-17-23/.137278|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 25, 2018|access-date=September 25, 2018|archive-date=March 14, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220314020451/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-25/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-september-17-23/.137278|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The fourth Blu-ray and DVD sets ranked fifth and sixth, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, October 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-23/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-october-15-21/.138513|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 23, 2018|access-date=October 23, 2018|archive-date=November 15, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115220708/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-23/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-october-15-21/.138513|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, October 15–21|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-23/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-october-15-21/.138515|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 23, 2018|access-date=October 23, 2018|archive-date=October 18, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211018115300/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-23/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-october-15-21/.138515|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The fifth Blu-ray set ranked third with 1,194 copies sold, while the DVD ranked second.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, November 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-20/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-november-12-18/.139750|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 20, 2018|access-date=November 20, 2018|archive-date=October 20, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211020143722/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-20/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-november-12-18/.139750|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, November 12–18|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-20/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-november-12-18/.139753|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 20, 2018|access-date=November 20, 2018|archive-date=January 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125030718/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-20/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-november-12-18/.139753|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The seventh Blu-ray and DVD sets ranked ninth and sixth, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, January 14–20|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-22/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-january-14-20/.142406|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 22, 2019|access-date=January 22, 2019|archive-date=December 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210012519/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-22/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-january-14-20/.142406|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, January 14–20|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-22/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-january-14-20/.142407|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 22, 2019|access-date=January 22, 2019|archive-date=September 30, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220930025803/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-22/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-january-14-20/.142407|url-status=live}}</p></ref> The eighth Blu-ray and DVD sets ranked fourth and third, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation Blu-ray Disc Ranking, February 11–17|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-19/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-february-11-17/.143622|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 19, 2019|access-date=February 19, 2019|archive-date=December 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210012513/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-19/japan-animation-blu-ray-disc-ranking-february-11-17/.143622|url-status=live}}</p><p>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Japan's Animation DVD Ranking, February 11–17|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-19/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-february-11-17/.143623|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 19, 2019|access-date=February 19, 2019|archive-date=August 16, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220816223924/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-19/japan-animation-dvd-ranking-february-11-17/.143623|url-status=live}}</p></ref> By the end of 2018, ''Bootleg'' became the top-selling anime CD album for the second consecutive year while ''LiSA BEST: Day'' ranked ninth on Oricon's chart.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Loo|first=Egan|title=Top-Selling Anime CD Albums: 2018|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-01/top-selling-anime-cd-albums-2018/.141066|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 1, 2019|access-date=January 1, 2021|archive-date=May 14, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514145043/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-01/top-selling-anime-cd-albums-2018/.141066|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== Critical reception ====
On [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the first season of ''My Hero Academia'' holds an approval rating of 100% based on ten reviews, with an average rating of 8.7/10.<ref>{{Cite Rotten Tomatoes|title=My Hero Academia|id=my_hero_academia_uncut|type=tv|season=1|access-date=April 26, 2024|archive-date=April 26, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240426145544/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/my_hero_academia_uncut/s01|url-status=live}}</ref> Alex Osborn of ''[[IGN]]'' gave the first season a nine out of ten rating, praising its action, story, and characters, while criticizing its villains as underdeveloped. Osborn also stated that "its excellent character design only elevates the memorable cast even further". He concluded that "the first season of ''My Hero Academia'' delivers thirteen episodes of fantastic action, elevated by a heartfelt story that's wrapped around a core cast of memorable and relatable characters".<ref name="season1">{{Cite web|last=Osborn|first=Alex|title=My Hero Academia: Season 1 Review|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/06/30/my-hero-academia-season-1-review|website=[[IGN]]|date=June 30, 2016|access-date=July 16, 2016|archive-date=July 9, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709224036/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/06/30/my-hero-academia-season-1-review|url-status=live}}</ref> In his review for the second season, Osborn praised it as "truly something special", complimenting the animation, character developments, and emotions. He called it as "one of the best TV shows" he had ever watched.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Osborn|first=Alex|title=My Hero Academia Season 2 Review|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/04/my-hero-academia-season-2-review|website=[[IGN]]|date=October 4, 2017|access-date=March 20, 2021|archive-date=November 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113221930/https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/04/my-hero-academia-season-2-review|url-status=live}}</ref> Tom Speelman of ''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]'' praised the anime for its animation, action and characters. Speelman also stated that compared to other superhero teams like ''[[X-Men]]'' or ''[[Legion of Super-Heroes]]'', ''My Hero Academia''{{'}}s biggest asset is its huge cast, with even minor characters having a "fun look" or "interesting personality" for readers to latch onto. He noted that it has similarities to the other shows and comics like ''[[Teen Titans (TV series)|Teen Titans]]'', ''[[Runaways (comics)|Runaways]]'', or ''[[Young Justice (TV series)|Young Justice]]'', though he felt its closest thematic analog is the 2005 Disney film ''[[Sky High (2005 film)|Sky High]]''.<ref name="my hero academia polygon">{{Cite web|last=Speelman|first=Tom|title=My Hero Academia: superhero fun without decades of backstory|url=https://www.polygon.com/tv/2017/6/5/15730554/my-hero-academia-explained|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|date=June 5, 2017|access-date=January 19, 2023|archive-date=January 27, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127042406/https://www.polygon.com/tv/2017/6/5/15730554/my-hero-academia-explained|url-status=live}}</ref> Chris Beveridge from ''The Fandom Post'' also praised the anime. He said that despite it being a long running series, it manages to not feel directionless and has several great moments.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Beveridge|first=Chris|title=My Hero Academia Season 1 Limited Edition Blu-Ray Anime Review|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2017/06/09/my-hero-academia-season-1-limited-edition-blu-ray-anime-review/|website=The Fandom Post|date=June 9, 2017|access-date=April 3, 2021|archive-date=January 28, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128191618/https://www.fandompost.com/2017/06/09/my-hero-academia-season-1-limited-edition-blu-ray-anime-review/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Nick Creamer of ''Anime News Network'' also praised the adaptation. He gave praise to the music and animation in the action scenes, while criticizing the pacing and stating that the animation can be average at times.<ref name="ANNAR">{{Cite web|last=Creamer|first=Nick|title=My Hero Academia BD+DVD – Season One [Limited Edition] Review|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia/bd-dvd-season-one-limited-edition/.117789|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 21, 2017|access-date=April 3, 2021|archive-date=January 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125104631/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia/bd-dvd-season-one-limited-edition/.117789|url-status=live}}</ref> In his review of the second season, he gave it praise for the improvements to both pacing and animation.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Creamer|first=Nick|title=My Hero Academia Season Two Part One Limited Edition BD/DVD|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia-season-two-part-one/limited-edition-bd/dvd/.132852|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 14, 2018|access-date=April 6, 2021|archive-date=January 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126000124/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia-season-two-part-one/limited-edition-bd/dvd/.132852|url-status=live}}</ref> Sam Leach of ''Anime News Network'' highlighted the 49th episode, which is the second battle between All Might and [[All For One (My Hero Academia)|All For One]]. Leach wrote: "It was unavoidable that this was going to be a beautiful episode. That bloodied-up All Might is striking in either form, and you can tell they pulled out all the stops in making the big hits as intense and crazy as possible. From a pacing perspective, I'm really pleased with how this Bakugo Rescue arc played out." He concluded: "This is ''My Hero Academia''{{'}}s proudest moment in the spotlight. Not only does it continue to be the darling of modern ''Shonen Jump'' with one of the mostly perfectly tuned anime adaptations a long-running series has ever received, this is an accomplishment of storytelling across the board."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Leach|first=Sam|title=My Hero Academia Episode 49|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia/episode-49/.133003|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 17, 2018|access-date=June 18, 2018|archive-date=June 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220624230019/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/my-hero-academia/episode-49/.133003|url-status=live}}</ref> Marina Garrow from ''Anime Feminist'' praised the way the plot handles damsel-in-distress elements, especially when compared to other {{Transliteration|ja|shōnen}} series, stating that the female characters are not the only characters that need saving, and when they do need saving, the situations are realistic and not overexaggerated.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Garrow|first=Marina|title=My Hero Academia Shows Us How To Write Damsels (And Dudes) In Distress|url=https://www.animefeminist.com/my-hero-academia-shows-us-how-to-write-damsels-and-dudes-in-distress/|website=Anime Feminist|date=March 27, 2020|access-date=April 6, 2021|archive-date=December 9, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201209000618/https://www.animefeminist.com/my-hero-academia-shows-us-how-to-write-damsels-and-dudes-in-distress/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Both the original Japanese cast and the English [[Dubbing|dub]] received praise from critics. Osborn applauded the casting choices and overall voice work, adding that [Izuku's voice actor] [[Daiki Yamashita]] is a "perfect fit" in the Japanese dub, while praising [[Justin Briner]]'s performance in English as excellent and standout.<ref name="season1"/> Creamer rated both equally, stating that the dub cast of the major characters generally fits their roles very well, though criticizing some of the background characters' performances.<ref name="ANNAR"/> Andy Hanley from ''UK Anime Network'' concured, stating both casts had strong performances; however, he gave special praise to the dub cast, saying that each actor fits their role very well.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hanley|first=Andy|title=My Hero Academia – Complete Season 1 Collector's Edition|url=http://www.uk-anime.net/Anime/My_Hero_Academia_-_Complete_Season_1_Collector's_Edition.html|website=UK Anime Network|date=May 17, 2017|access-date=April 6, 2021|archive-date=November 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128113050/http://uk-anime.net/Anime/My_Hero_Academia_-_Complete_Season_1_Collector%27s_Edition.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Speelman stated that both Japanese and English casts know exactly how to make these roles work. He noted that both Yamashita and Briner's voice as Izuku "nail the optimistic nerdiness and heroic attitude", with Briner "channeling a bit of [[Morty Smith]] for good measure". He also praised the voice performances of All Might, noting that Japanese voice actor [[Kenta Miyake]] "nails the goofy earnestness of the part", while English voice actor Christopher Sabat "was essentially [[Superman]]", Speelman felt was a "great fit".<ref name="my hero academia polygon"/>

The anime series has been named as one of the best of the 2010s in several publications. Writing for ''[[Comic Book Resources]]'', Sage Ashford ranked it fourth on his list, praising its character development. Although he criticized the series' perceived lack of originality, he felt it executes the classic {{Transliteration|ja|shōnen}} tropes perfectly, describing it as the "most finely tuned battle shonen ever created".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ashford|first=Sage|title=10 Best Anime Series of the Last Decade, Ranked|url=https://www.cbr.com/anime-best-series-last-decade-ranked/|website=[[Comic Book Resources]]|date=November 27, 2019|access-date=December 3, 2019|archive-date=December 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203192547/https://www.cbr.com/anime-best-series-last-decade-ranked/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'' ranked ''My Hero Academia'' among the top 50 anime of all time.<ref>{{Cite web|title=The 50 Best Anime Series of All Time|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/tv/anime/the-50-best-anime-series-of-all-time/#39-my-hero-academia|website=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=October 3, 2018|access-date=May 12, 2020|archive-date=April 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418163240/https://www.pastemagazine.com/tv/anime/the-50-best-anime-series-of-all-time/#39-my-hero-academia|url-status=dead}}</ref> In November 2019, ''Polygon'' named it as one of the best anime of the 2010s,<ref>{{Cite web|title=The best anime of the decade|url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/11/6/20948241/best-new-anime-of-the-decade-2010s|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|date=November 6, 2019|access-date=November 17, 2019|archive-date=December 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220154644/https://www.polygon.com/2019/11/6/20948241/best-new-anime-of-the-decade-2010s|url-status=live}}</ref> and Crunchyroll listed it in their "Top 25 best anime of the 2010s".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wolf|first=Ian|title=Crunchyroll Names The Top 100 Anime of the 2010s|url=http://animeuknews.net/2019/11/crunchyroll-names-the-top-100-anime-of-the-2010s/|website=Anime UK News|date=November 27, 2019|access-date=November 27, 2019|archive-date=November 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191127213200/http://animeuknews.net/2019/11/crunchyroll-names-the-top-100-anime-of-the-2010s/|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2020, ''IGN'' and ''[[Thrillist]]'' named it among the best anime series of the 2010s.<ref>Best Anime Series of 2010s:
* {{Cite web|title=The Best Anime of the Decade (2010–2019)|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2020/01/01/best-anime-of-the-decade-2010-2019|website=[[IGN]]|access-date=January 4, 2020|date=January 1, 2020|archive-date=January 1, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101214124/https://www.ign.com/articles/2020/01/01/best-anime-of-the-decade-2010-2019|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|title=The Best Anime of the 2010s|url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/best-anime-of-the-decade-2010s|website=[[Thrillist]]|date=January 3, 2020|access-date=February 13, 2020|archive-date=February 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205154012/https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/best-anime-of-the-decade-2010s|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Japan Web Magazine'' ranked the series 24th on its list of "30 Best Anime of All Time".<ref>{{Cite web|title=30 Best Anime of All Time (2020)|url=https://jw-webmagazine.com/best-anime/|website=Japan Web Magazine|publisher=Inbound Platform Corp|date=March 25, 2020|access-date=October 25, 2020|archive-date=October 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028212611/https://jw-webmagazine.com/best-anime/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== Accolades ====
At the [[1st Crunchyroll Anime Awards|Crunchyroll's inaugural Anime Awards]] in 2017, Izuku was awarded "[[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Character#Best Protagonist|Hero of the Year]]" while the anime series was nominated in six other categories including "[[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Anime of the Year|Anime of the Year]]".<ref name="1stCRAA"/> In December 2017, the second season of ''My Hero Academia'' was among the Top 100 Favorites nominated for Anime of the Year at the [[Tokyo Anime Award|Tokyo Anime Award Festival 2018]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://best100.animefestival.jp/finish.html|title=みんなが選ぶベスト100 {{sic|nolink=y|Animes}} of 2017|publisher=[[Tokyo Anime Award Festival]]|access-date=March 15, 2018|archive-date=December 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171226234658/https://best100.animefestival.jp/finish.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> At the [[2nd Crunchyroll Anime Awards]] in 2018, the season won seven out of ten nominations: [[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Action|Best Action]], [[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Animation|Best Animation]], [[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Opening Sequence|Best Opening]] ("Peace Sign"), [[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Character#Best Girl|Best Girl]] ([[Ochaco Uraraka]]), [[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Character#Best Boy|Best Boy]] (Shoto Todoroki), [[Crunchyroll Anime Award for Best Character#Best Antagonist|Best Villain]] ([[Stain (My Hero Academia)|Stain]]), and Best Hero (Izuku Midoriya) categories; [[Christopher Sabat]] also received the Industry Icon Award for his role as [[All Might]].<ref name="2ndCRAA"/> The series ranked first in a "mega poll" of the readers for Best Anime of 2017 and 2018 by ''Anime News Network''.<ref>Best Anime Mega Poll:
* {{Cite web|title=The Best Anime of 2017 MEGA POLL|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/survey/756/result|website=[[Anime News Network]]|access-date=January 1, 2018|archive-date=October 19, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211019223326/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/survey/756/result|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|title=The Best Anime of 2018 MEGA POLL|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/survey/816/result|website=[[Anime News Network]]|access-date=April 3, 2019|archive-date=May 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220501232516/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/survey/816/result|url-status=live}}</ref>

''My Hero Academia'' won "Shonen Series of the Decade" at the [[Funimation]]'s Decade of Anime poll, where the fans voted for their favorite anime across multiple categories.<ref name="FunimationDecadeofAnime"/> In the other fan poll, Izuku Midoriya and Shoto Todoroki were chosen as one of the "Best Boys of the Decade", while Ochaco Uraraka became one of the five recipients for the "Best Girls of the Decade" category.<ref name="BestBoys&Girls"/> In 2021, the series won the "Most In-Demand Anime Series of 2020" at the third Global TV Demand Awards;<ref name="3rdGTVDA"/> it won the same category at the seventh Global Demand Awards in 2025, while being one of the finalists for "Most In-Demand TV Series in the World 2024".<ref name="7thGDA"/> In 2023, the series along with ''[[Attack on Titan (TV series)|Attack on Titan]]'', became the first anime to receive an [[Hollywood Creative Alliance|Astra TV Award]] nomination for "Best Streaming Animated Series or TV Movie" at the [[1st Astra Creative Arts TV Awards|inaugural Astra Creative Arts TV Awards]].<ref name="AstraTVAwards"/>

